Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me provide the exhaustive integration test suite design.

---

## Exhaustive Integration Test Suite Design for ASG

### Executive Summary

Based on exploration of the ASG codebase, I propose a comprehensive integration test suite organized by feature area, using small, purpose-built test ontologies. The design follows the existing patterns from `SimpleApiIT` and `LargeApiIT` while systematically covering all 16 restriction types, 46 XSD datatype mappings, 3 property types, configuration options, and annotations.

---

### 1. Test Organization Strategy

**Organization: Hybrid by Feature Area + OWL Construct**

Tests should be organized into test classes by feature area, with nested classes for related OWL constructs:

```
src/test/java/regression/
  features/
    restrictions/
      CardinalityRestrictionsIT.java      # Object + Data cardinality tests
      ValueRestrictionsIT.java            # SomeValuesFrom, AllValuesFrom, HasValue, OneOf
      BooleanRestrictionsIT.java          # UnionOf, IntersectionOf, ComplementOf
    datatypes/
      StringDatatypesIT.java              # string, anyURI, base64Binary, etc.
      NumericDatatypesIT.java             # integer, decimal, float, double, etc.
      TemporalDatatypesIT.java            # date, dateTime, time, duration
      MiscDatatypesIT.java                # boolean, byte, specialized types
    properties/
      DataPropertyIT.java                 # Data property mapping
      ObjectPropertyIT.java               # Object property with $ref, x-grl-model-link
      TaxonomyPropertyIT.java             # Enum from named individuals
    configuration/
      ConfigInheritanceIT.java            # extends, variable substitution
      NamespaceMappingIT.java             # namespaceMappings
      SecurityConfigIT.java               # security templates, mappings
      TemplateIT.java                     # OpenAPI templates
    annotations/
      AnnotationMappingIT.java            # apiLabel, skos:prefLabel, etc.
    output/
      PathGenerationIT.java               # Collection/single endpoints
      SchemaCompositionIT.java            # allOf, anyOf, oneOf
```

---

### 2. Test Ontologies Specification

Each ontology should be minimal, focused on one specific feature area.

#### 2.1 Ontology File Structure

```
src/test/resources/regression/
  ontologies/
    restrictions/
      cardinality-test.owl          # All cardinality restrictions
      value-restrictions-test.owl   # SomeValuesFrom, AllValuesFrom, etc.
      boolean-combinations-test.owl # UnionOf, IntersectionOf, ComplementOf
    datatypes/
      string-types-test.owl         # All string-family XSD types
      numeric-types-test.owl        # All numeric XSD types
      temporal-types-test.owl       # date, dateTime, time, duration
      misc-types-test.owl           # boolean, byte, other types
    properties/
      data-property-test.owl        # Various data property scenarios
      object-property-test.owl      # Object refs, arrays, x-grl-model-link
      taxonomy-test.owl             # Named individuals as enum values
    configuration/
      inheritance-base.owl          # Base for config inheritance tests
      namespace-test.owl            # Multiple namespaces for flattening
      security-test.owl             # Classes needing security scopes
    annotations/
      annotation-test.owl           # All annotation types on properties
    output/
      path-generation-test.owl      # Multiple resources for path tests
  configs/
    restrictions/
      config-cardinality.yaml
      config-value-restrictions.yaml
      config-boolean-combinations.yaml
    datatypes/
      config-string-types.yaml
      config-numeric-types.yaml
      config-temporal-types.yaml
      config-misc-types.yaml
    properties/
      config-data-property.yaml
      config-object-property.yaml
      config-taxonomy.yaml
    configuration/
      config-base-inheritance.yaml
      config-child-inheritance.yaml
      config-namespace.yaml
      config-security.yaml
    annotations/
      config-annotations.yaml
    output/
      config-path-generation.yaml
```

---

### 3. Detailed Test Ontology Designs

#### 3.1 Cardinality Restrictions Ontology (`cardinality-test.owl`)

**Purpose:** Test all 6 cardinality restriction types

**Classes:**
- `CardinalityTestAPI` - root API class
- `CardinalityResource` - test resource with all cardinality types

**Properties and Restrictions:**

```turtle
:CardinalityResource rdfs:subClassOf [
    owl:onProperty :hasMinOneItem ;
    owl:minCardinality 1
] .

:CardinalityResource rdfs:subClassOf [
    owl:onProperty :hasMaxFiveItems ;
    owl:maxCardinality 5
] .

:CardinalityResource rdfs:subClassOf [
    owl:onProperty :hasExactlyThreeItems ;
    owl:cardinality 3
] .

:CardinalityResource rdfs:subClassOf [
    owl:onProperty :hasDataMinTwo ;
    owl:minCardinality 2 ;
    owl:onDataRange xsd:string
] .

:CardinalityResource rdfs:subClassOf [
    owl:onProperty :hasDataMaxTen ;
    owl:maxCardinality 10 ;
    owl:onDataRange xsd:integer
] .

:CardinalityResource rdfs:subClassOf [
    owl:onProperty :hasDataExactlyOne ;
    owl:qualifiedCardinality 1 ;
    owl:onDataRange xsd:string
] .
```

**Expected OpenAPI Output Tests:**
- `minItems: 1` for MinCardinality
- `maxItems: 5` for MaxCardinality
- `minItems: 3, maxItems: 3` for ExactCardinality
- Required field when minCardinality >= 1
- Array type when cardinality > 1

---

#### 3.2 Value Restrictions Ontology (`value-restrictions-test.owl`)

**Purpose:** Test SomeValuesFrom, AllValuesFrom, HasValue, OneOf, and data variants

**Classes:**
- `ValueRestrictionsAPI` - root
- `ValueRestrictionsResource`
- `TargetClass` - range class for object properties

**Restrictions:**

```turtle
:ValueRestrictionsResource rdfs:subClassOf [
    owl:onProperty :hasSomeTarget ;
    owl:someValuesFrom :TargetClass
] .

:ValueRestrictionsResource rdfs:subClassOf [
    owl:onProperty :hasOnlyTarget ;
    owl:allValuesFrom :TargetClass
] .

:ValueRestrictionsResource rdfs:subClassOf [
    owl:onProperty :hasSpecificValue ;
    owl:hasValue :individualA
] .

:ValueRestrictionsResource rdfs:subClassOf [
    owl:onProperty :hasOneOfValues ;
    owl:someValuesFrom [
        owl:oneOf (:optionA :optionB :optionC)
    ]
] .

# Data variants
:ValueRestrictionsResource rdfs:subClassOf [
    owl:onProperty :hasDataSome ;
    owl:someValuesFrom xsd:string
] .

:ValueRestrictionsResource rdfs:subClassOf [
    owl:onProperty :hasDataAll ;
    owl:allValuesFrom xsd:integer
] .

:ValueRestrictionsResource rdfs:subClassOf [
    owl:onProperty :hasDataDefaultValue ;
    owl:hasValue "default"^^xsd:string
] .

:ValueRestrictionsResource rdfs:subClassOf [
    owl:onProperty :hasEnumValues ;
    owl:someValuesFrom [
        owl:oneOf ("value1"^^xsd:string "value2"^^xsd:string "value3"^^xsd:string)
    ]
] .
```

**Expected Tests:**
- SomeValuesFrom implies required, minItems: 1 for arrays
- AllValuesFrom is type constraint only (no cardinality)
- HasValue sets default
- DataOneOf creates enum

---

#### 3.3 Boolean Combinations Ontology (`boolean-combinations-test.owl`)

**Purpose:** Test UnionOf, IntersectionOf, ComplementOf

**Classes:**
- `BooleanCombinationsAPI`
- `BooleanResource`
- `TypeA`, `TypeB`, `TypeC` - range classes

**Restrictions:**

```turtle
:BooleanResource rdfs:subClassOf [
    owl:onProperty :hasUnionType ;
    owl:someValuesFrom [
        owl:unionOf (:TypeA :TypeB)
    ]
] .

:BooleanResource rdfs:subClassOf [
    owl:onProperty :hasIntersectionType ;
    owl:someValuesFrom [
        owl:intersectionOf (:TypeA :TypeB)
    ]
] .

:BooleanResource rdfs:subClassOf [
    owl:onProperty :hasNotType ;
    owl:someValuesFrom [
        owl:complementOf :TypeC
    ]
] .

# Data union/intersection
:BooleanResource rdfs:subClassOf [
    owl:onProperty :hasDataUnion ;
    owl:someValuesFrom [
        owl:unionOf (xsd:string xsd:integer)
    ]
] .
```

**Expected Tests:**
- UnionOf creates anyOf composed schema
- IntersectionOf creates allOf composed schema
- ComplementOf creates not schema
- Array contains composed items

---

#### 3.4 XSD Datatypes Ontologies

##### 3.4.1 String Types (`string-types-test.owl`)

Test all string-family XSD types:

| XSD Type | OpenAPI Type | Format | Example |
|----------|--------------|--------|---------|
| string | string | - | "string value" |
| anyURI | string | uri | "http://example.com" |
